Dialogue: 0.0:00:10.02.0:00:12.52.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}Computer. dispatches.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:12.53.0:00:14.03.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.408)}A research inquiry
Dialogue: 0.0:00:14.03.0:00:16.53.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.408)}\hfrom the {\i1}Manitoba Journal\Nof Interplanetary Psychology
Dialogue: 0.0:00:16.53.0:00:19.53.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.408)}and three communiqués\N\h\hfrom your mother.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:19.53.0:00:21.04.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}( {\i1}sighs{\r} )
Dialogue: 0.0:00:23.04.0:00:26.04.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}\hTransfer the letters from\Nmy mother to the viewscreen.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:30.04.0:00:35.54.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}And. computer. I would like\N\h\ha real chocolate sundae.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:35.55.0:00:39.55.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.408)}Define "real" in context.\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hplease.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:39.55.0:00:40.56.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}Real.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:40.55.0:00:44.05.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}\h\h\hNot one of your\Nperfectly synthesized
Dialogue: 0.0:00:44.06.0:00:46.56.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}ingeniously enhanced imitations.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:49.06.0:00:52.07.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\hI would like\Nreal chocolate ice cream
Dialogue: 0.0:00:52.06.0:00:54.06.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}real whipped cream...
Dialogue: 0.0:00:54.07.0:00:55.57.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.408)}This unit is programmed
Dialogue: 0.0:00:56.07.0:00:58.57.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.408)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hto provide sources\Nof acceptable nutritional value.
Dialogue: 0.0:00:58.57.0:01:01.99.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.408)}Your request does not fall\Nwithin current guidelines.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:01.99.0:01:04.50.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.408)}Please indicate whether you wish
Dialogue: 0.0:01:04.49.0:01:06.49.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.408)}\h\h\h\h\hto override\Nthe specified program.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:06.50.0:01:08.00.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}Listen...
Dialogue: 0.0:01:08.00.0:01:11.00.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.408)}Picard to Counselor Troi.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:11.00.0:01:13.00.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}Now what?
Dialogue: 0.0:01:13.00.0:01:14.51.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.432)}Yes. Captain?
Dialogue: 0.0:01:14.50.0:01:17.43.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}The pleasure of your company\N\h\his requested. Counselor.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:17.44.0:01:19.44.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}\hWe are. um... we're having\Na little impromptu reception
Dialogue: 0.0:01:19.44.0:01:20.70.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}for the arriving delegates.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:20.69.0:01:23.02.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Captain. I'm not really dressed\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hfor a reception.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:23.03.0:01:24.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.408)}Oh. Counselor
Dialogue: 0.0:01:24.31.0:01:26.11.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}just throw on any old thing.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:26.12.0:01:28.12.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWe're about to get\Nour first look at the wormhole.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:28.62.0:01:29.62.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.408)}Of course. Captain.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:29.62.0:01:30.62.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.408)}I'm on my way.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:33.92.0:01:38.22.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}\h\h\hGod forbid I should miss\Nmy first look at the wormhole.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:42.60.0:01:44.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}May I escort\Nyou. Miss Troi?
Dialogue: 0.0:01:44.10.0:01:46.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Just tell me there's\Nsome chocolate here.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:46.10.0:01:47.61.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}PICARD:\NAh. Counselor Troi.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:47.60.0:01:50.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Will you allow me to do\N\h\h\hthe introductions?
Dialogue: 0.0:01:50.11.0:01:52.11.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}This is Premier Bhavani\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\hof Barzan.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:52.11.0:01:53.61.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}Counselor Deanna Troi.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:53.61.0:01:55.05.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Your discovery has produced
Dialogue: 0.0:01:55.04.0:01:57.26.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}a great deal of excitement.\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hPremier.
Dialogue: 0.0:01:57.26.0:01:59.02.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Hopefully. it will\Nalso produce
Dialogue: 0.0:01:59.03.0:02:01.54.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}a new era of prosperity\Nfor my people.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:01.53.0:02:03.36.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}We'll see to that.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:03.37.0:02:06.04.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}\h\hYou know Mr. Mendoza.\Nthe Federation negotiator.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:06.04.0:02:08.61.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}A pleasure to see you again.\N\h\h\h\h\h\hCounselor Troi.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:10.69.0:02:13.30.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}This is a worthy Federation\Ncompetitor in the bidding
Dialogue: 0.0:02:13.31.0:02:14.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Leyor of the Caldonians.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:14.31.0:02:15.56.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}Madam.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:15.56.0:02:18.73.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hMAN:\NAnd I am Devinoni Ral.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:20.95.0:02:24.13.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}Ship's Counselor Deanna Troi.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:24.14.0:02:26.41.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}\h\h\h\h\hMENDOZA:\NMy good friend Ral
Dialogue: 0.0:02:26.41.0:02:29.11.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}is the best hired gun\N\h\h\hin the business.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:29.11.0:02:31.43.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}Hired gun?
Dialogue: 0.0:02:31.43.0:02:34.75.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}My good friend Mendoza means\N\h\h\hthat I'm a negotiator
Dialogue: 0.0:02:34.75.0:02:37.26.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}who serves a variety of clients.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:37.25.0:02:40.25.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}On this particular occasion.\NI represent the Chrysalians.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:40.26.0:02:42.71.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hBHAVANI:\NI believe it's almost time.\N\h\h\h\h\hisn't it. Captain?
Dialogue: 0.0:02:42.71.0:02:44.21.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(496.432)}Indeed.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:44.21.0:02:46.71.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}It will be visible\Ndirectly ahead.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:52.13.0:02:53.63.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}Is it always on time. Bhavani?
Dialogue: 0.0:02:53.64.0:02:54.64.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Always.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:54.64.0:02:57.56.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}We see it every 233 minutes.
Dialogue: 0.0:02:57.56.0:02:59.33.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}Our scientists say
Dialogue: 0.0:02:59.32.0:03:03.81.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}it's due to radiation buildup\Nin the accretion disk.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:03.81.0:03:08.43.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}The visible burst\Nis very brief.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:10.74.0:03:13.74.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}There it is. ladies and\Ngentlemen. the first
Dialogue: 0.0:03:13.74.0:03:17.58.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}and only stable wormhole\Nknown to exist.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:17.58.0:03:21.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}It's yours.\Nfor the right price.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:54.15.0:03:58.65.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}{\i1}Space. the final frontier.
Dialogue: 0.0:03:58.65.0:04:02.66.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}\h\h\h{\i1}These are the voyages\Nof the Starship{\r} Enterprise.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:02.65.0:04:04.65.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}{\i1}Its continuing mission--
Dialogue: 0.0:04:04.66.0:04:08.66.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}\h\h\h\h{\i1}to explore\Nstrange new worlds
Dialogue: 0.0:04:08.66.0:04:13.17.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}{\i1}to seek out new life\Nand new civilizations
Dialogue: 0.0:04:13.17.0:04:17.64.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h{\i1}to boldly go\Nwhere no one has gone before.
Dialogue: 0.0:04:17.64.0:04:21.71.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}[Captioning sponsored by\N\h\hPARAMOUNT PICTURES]
Dialogue: 0.0:05:17.20.0:05:20.23.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}\h{\i1}Captain's Log.\NStardate 43385.6.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:20.23.0:05:23.24.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.120)}{\i1}We are orbiting Barzan II.\Nwhich is entertaining bids
Dialogue: 0.0:05:23.24.0:05:26.24.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.120)}{\i1}for control of what appears\N\h\hto be a stable wormhole
Dialogue: 0.0:05:26.24.0:05:28.74.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.120)}{\i1}which could provide\Na permanent shortcut
Dialogue: 0.0:05:28.74.0:05:30.58.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.96)}{\i1}to the distant Gamma Quadrant.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:30.58.0:05:34.45.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.120)}As you all know. the\Nenvironment on my planet
Dialogue: 0.0:05:34.45.0:05:37.95.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.120)}is completely inhospitable\Nto most other life-forms.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:37.95.0:05:41.92.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.120)}So I'd like to express\Nmy appreciation to you
Dialogue: 0.0:05:41.92.0:05:43.21.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.96)}Captain Picard
Dialogue: 0.0:05:43.21.0:05:45.76.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.120)}for hosting\Nthese negotiations.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:45.76.0:05:48.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(388.120)}The Barzan has\Nbeen a society
Dialogue: 0.0:05:48.09.0:05:50.91.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.120)}dependent on others\Nfor generations.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:50.91.0:05:53.21.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.96)}We want that to end.
Dialogue: 0.0:05:53.22.0:05:57.47.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.120)}The appearance of this stable\N\h\h\h\hwormhole in our space
Dialogue: 0.0:05:57.47.0:06:01.04.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.120)}provides us with our first\Ntrue natural resource.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:01.04.0:06:04.05.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.96)}We have neither the experience
Dialogue: 0.0:06:04.04.0:06:07.37.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.120)}nor the technology\N\h\hto exploit it.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:07.38.0:06:08.77.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.96)}But you do.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:08.76.0:06:10.51.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.120)}RIKER:\NExcuse me.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:10.52.0:06:11.85.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.96)}There's a delegation of Ferengi
Dialogue: 0.0:06:11.85.0:06:13.22.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.120)}\hthat wishes to be\Nbeamed aboard. sir.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:15.45.0:06:18.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.120)}Were you expecting the Ferengi.\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hPremier?
Dialogue: 0.0:06:18.32.0:06:21.29.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.120)}\h\h\hNo. but I do not wish\Nto create ill will. Captain.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:21.29.0:06:25.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.120)}\h\hIf they are interested in\Nbidding. I have no objection.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:27.30.0:06:29.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.120)}\h\h\h\h\hChief O'Brien.\Nthis is Captain Picard.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:30.19.0:06:31.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.96)}Will you beam the Ferengi
Dialogue: 0.0:06:31.19.0:06:32.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.120)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hdirectly\Nto the observation lounge?
Dialogue: 0.0:06:33.19.0:06:34.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.120)}Aye. sir.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:40.05.0:06:42.05.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}On behalf of all Ferengi.\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hI protest.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:42.05.0:06:45.05.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Why were we not invited\Nto these negotiations?
Dialogue: 0.0:06:45.05.0:06:46.39.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}BHAVANI:\NMy apologies.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:46.39.0:06:48.26.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}We did not anticipate\N\h\h\h\hyour interest.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:48.25.0:06:49.25.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}You're welcome to join us.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:49.25.0:06:52.20.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}My name is DaiMon Goss
Dialogue: 0.0:06:52.21.0:06:55.71.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}and these are my consuls--\NKol and Dr. Arridor.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:56.21.0:06:57.22.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}We'll need chairs.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:57.21.0:06:59.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(316.432)}I'm Captain Picard\Nof the {\i1}Enterprise.
Dialogue: 0.0:06:59.70.0:07:01.09.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}I am serving as host\Nfor these proceedings.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:01.08.0:07:02.53.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}Good.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:02.53.0:07:03.33.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}\h\h\hThen see to it\Nwe get some chairs.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:03.34.0:07:05.02.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Let me explain...
Dialogue: 0.0:07:05.02.0:07:06.86.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}Fine. fine-- just have\N\hyour Klingon servant
Dialogue: 0.0:07:07.36.0:07:08.11.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}get us some chairs.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:08.11.0:07:09.81.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I'm in charge of security.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:09.81.0:07:12.51.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}Then who gets the chairs?
Dialogue: 0.0:07:12.51.0:07:15.83.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}DaiMon. due to\Nthe delicate nature
Dialogue: 0.0:07:15.83.0:07:19.17.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}of these negotiations.\Nall parties
Dialogue: 0.0:07:19.17.0:07:21.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}have agreed that one\Nrepresentative will suffice.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:21.45.0:07:23.70.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Now. I will be\Nhappy to provide
Dialogue: 0.0:07:23.71.0:07:26.59.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(334.432)}your consuls with\Naccommodations
Dialogue: 0.0:07:26.59.0:07:28.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}and {\i1}you{\r} may have {\i1}my{\r} chair.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:28.46.0:07:30.38.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Very well.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:30.38.0:07:31.63.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(496.432)}Premier.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:40.52.0:07:42.82.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Kol. the bag.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:42.82.0:07:44.82.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}RIKER:\NGentlemen. this way.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:44.83.0:07:47.58.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWe can handle\Nall the pleasantries later.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:47.58.0:07:49.90.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Now. let's get\Ndown to business.
Dialogue: 0.0:07:52.17.0:07:54.47.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}I'll match anyone's best offer
Dialogue: 0.0:07:54.47.0:07:56.67.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}and add the gold
Dialogue: 0.0:07:56.67.0:07:59.21.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}on top of it.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:00.51.0:08:02.35.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}( {\i1}chuckles{\r} )
Dialogue: 0.0:08:02.34.0:08:05.26.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.408)}Devinoni Ral. human. age 41.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:05.26.0:08:08.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.408)}\h\hBorn Brussels.\NEuropean Alliance.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:08.20.0:08:11.71.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.408)}Relocated at age 19\N\h\hto Hurkos III...
Dialogue: 0.0:08:11.70.0:08:12.70.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}( {\i1}door chimes{\r} )
Dialogue: 0.0:08:12.70.0:08:13.70.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Come in.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:20.85.0:08:22.68.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}\h\h\hShould I call\Nfor an appointment?
Dialogue: 0.0:08:22.68.0:08:27.59.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}No. I was just looking\Nover some personnel files.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:27.59.0:08:29.09.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Well. that's too bad.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:29.09.0:08:32.09.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}I thought you might\Nbe thinking about me.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:32.09.0:08:35.60.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I thought you'd be deep\Nin negotiations by now.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:35.59.0:08:37.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}In recess.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:37.35.0:08:41.45.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hI never play\Nthe opening rounds. anyway.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:41.45.0:08:42.95.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Inconsequential.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:42.95.0:08:45.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}Besides. there are\Nmuch better things
Dialogue: 0.0:08:45.45.0:08:47.25.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}to negotiate on this ship...
Dialogue: 0.0:08:47.26.0:08:51.13.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}like dinner tonight.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:51.13.0:08:53.88.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}What about your\Ntraveling companion?
Dialogue: 0.0:08:53.88.0:08:58.80.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}My traveling companion\N\h\h\his... traveling.
Dialogue: 0.0:08:58.80.0:09:02.17.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}I sent her home.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:02.17.0:09:04.68.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Why?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:04.67.0:09:07.67.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}You know why.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:07.68.0:09:11.18.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Weren't you getting along?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:11.18.0:09:12.68.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Don't do that.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:12.68.0:09:13.68.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(496.432)}What?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:14.18.0:09:17.18.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Don't do "Counselor" Troi.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:17.19.0:09:18.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(496.432)}Was I?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:18.69.0:09:21.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Yes. you were.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:26.19.0:09:29.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}When you leave this office
Dialogue: 0.0:09:29.70.0:09:32.70.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}who are you?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:33.20.0:09:36.21.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}Oh. so that's how it goes?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:36.20.0:09:40.12.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}You never do.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:40.13.0:09:41.63.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}You never do...
Dialogue: 0.0:09:41.63.0:09:45.13.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}leave the office.
Dialogue: 0.0:09:45.13.0:09:46.63.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}What are...?
Dialogue: 0.0:09:46.63.0:09:48.14.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Shh-shh-shh-shh-shh...
Dialogue: 0.0:10:02.03.0:10:04.49.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Dinner at 8:00?
Dialogue: 0.0:10:09.99.0:10:13.49.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}( {\i1}door opens and closes{\r} )
Dialogue: 0.0:10:22.97.0:10:26.27.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}The readings from the Barzans'\Nprobe of the wormhole
Dialogue: 0.0:10:26.27.0:10:27.78.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}are quite impressive.\NCaptain.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:28.27.0:10:31.15.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}The wormhole delivered\Nthe probe beyond the Denkiri Arm
Dialogue: 0.0:10:31.16.0:10:32.65.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}in the Gamma Quadrant.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:32.64.0:10:34.94.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}( {\i1}whistles{\r} )
Dialogue: 0.0:10:34.95.0:10:37.80.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}It would take nearly\Na century at warp 9
Dialogue: 0.0:10:37.80.0:10:39.30.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}to cover\Nthat distance.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:39.30.0:10:41.31.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}The same distance\Ncould be achieved
Dialogue: 0.0:10:41.30.0:10:43.80.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}in a matter of seconds\Nthrough the wormhole.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:43.81.0:10:47.31.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Imagine the Ferengi\Ncollecting tolls\Nif we lose to them.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:47.31.0:10:48.81.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}I don't think the Ferengi
Dialogue: 0.0:10:48.81.0:10:51.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}are the greatest threat\N\h\h\h\h\hat the table.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:51.31.0:10:53.31.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}With all of DaiMon Goss' bluster
Dialogue: 0.0:10:53.32.0:10:56.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}they don't have the resources\N\h\h\h\h\h\hthe Barzans need.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:56.32.0:10:57.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(496.432)}Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0.0:10:57.32.0:10:58.82.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}I think that Devinoni
Dialogue: 0.0:10:58.82.0:11:01.33.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}is the one we need\Nto watch out for.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:01.32.0:11:03.12.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}An accurate observation.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:03.12.0:11:05.04.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}How did you\Nrecognize that?
Dialogue: 0.0:11:05.04.0:11:06.87.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}\h\h\h\hWell. he was the most\Ncomfortable one in the group.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:06.88.0:11:08.70.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}You must play poker. Commander.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:08.70.0:11:12.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hPoker?\NIs that a game of some sort?
Dialogue: 0.0:11:12.18.0:11:15.48.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Commander Riker conducts\Nmaster classes in poker.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:15.49.0:11:17.44.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(388.432)}Our skills are
Dialogue: 0.0:11:17.44.0:11:19.41.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}not dissimilar. Commander.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:19.41.0:11:22.91.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Mr. Mendoza. if this\Nlives up to its billing
Dialogue: 0.0:11:22.91.0:11:26.42.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}it will be a discovery\Nof extraordinary value
Dialogue: 0.0:11:26.92.0:11:29.17.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}but it is\Na very big "if."
Dialogue: 0.0:11:29.17.0:11:31.01.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}A wormhole is there one moment\N\h\h\hand then gone the next.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:31.50.0:11:33.38.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}A stable wormhole is unheard of.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:33.39.0:11:35.83.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hAre you saying\Nthis may not be what it seems?
Dialogue: 0.0:11:35.82.0:11:38.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}The Barzans do not have\Nmanned space travel
Dialogue: 0.0:11:38.33.0:11:40.83.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}so they had to resort\Nto an automated probe.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:40.83.0:11:42.33.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Its findings are limited.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:42.33.0:11:44.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}It cannot be determined\Nfrom these charts
Dialogue: 0.0:11:44.33.0:11:46.33.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}how stable the wormhole\Nreally is
Dialogue: 0.0:11:46.33.0:11:48.33.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}or how long it will\Nremain intact.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:48.34.0:11:50.84.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}The Federation\Ncould end up buying
Dialogue: 0.0:11:50.84.0:11:52.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}a proverbial lemon.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:52.34.0:11:54.35.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}"Proverbial lemon"?
Dialogue: 0.0:11:54.34.0:11:55.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}Later. Data.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:55.34.0:11:56.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Aye. sir.
Dialogue: 0.0:11:56.34.0:11:57.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}And. of course. that means
Dialogue: 0.0:11:57.85.0:11:59.85.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}once the contract is\Nnegotiated and closed
Dialogue: 0.0:11:59.85.0:12:02.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}\hwe would be obliged\Nto fulfill the terms.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:02.10.0:12:04.14.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}\h\h\h\hI think we should\Ntake a look for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:04.14.0:12:06.01.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}I don't think Bhavani\Ncould object to that.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:06.00.0:12:08.00.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Geordi has been\Nin continuous visual contact
Dialogue: 0.0:12:08.01.0:12:09.51.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}with the wormhole. Captain.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:09.51.0:12:10.51.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I think he's\Na logical choice.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:10.51.0:12:12.51.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}I would also like\Nto volunteer. sir.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:13.01.0:12:14.52.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}Hmm. Nobody's\Ngoing in there
Dialogue: 0.0:12:14.51.0:12:16.81.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}until we have done\Na full sensor analysis.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:16.82.0:12:20.22.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I want to do everything possible\N\h\hto determine that it is safe
Dialogue: 0.0:12:20.22.0:12:22.02.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}and when I am satisfied.\N\h\h\h\h\hthen you. Data
Dialogue: 0.0:12:22.02.0:12:24.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.432)}and Commander La Forge\Nwill enter the wormhole
Dialogue: 0.0:12:24.69.0:12:27.06.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:27.06.0:12:31.93.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Just a moment of discomfort\Nfor a good cause. DaiMon.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:32.43.0:12:35.94.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}You understand this\Nwill not be lethal?
Dialogue: 0.0:12:35.93.0:12:37.43.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}Doctor. you\Nsurprise me.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:37.94.0:12:39.94.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}I have no wish\Nto kill anyone.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:39.94.0:12:42.94.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}A short-term crippling\Nwill suffice.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:42.94.0:12:45.45.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Then. this will\Nbe just fine.
Dialogue: 0.0:12:45.44.0:12:49.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}A distillation of your\Nown blood pyrocytes--
Dialogue: 0.0:12:49.20.0:12:53.47.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}harmless to you. undetectable\Nby the ship's bio-filters
Dialogue: 0.0:12:53.47.0:12:56.97.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}but. when absorbed\Nthrough your victim's skin
Dialogue: 0.0:12:56.97.0:13:00.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}it will provoke\Nan extreme allergic reaction.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:00.46.0:13:03.96.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}I'd say it's time to extend\Nthe hand of the Ferengi
Dialogue: 0.0:13:04.46.0:13:07.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}to the Representative\Nof the Federation.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:07.47.0:13:10.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}( {\i1}cackling giggles{\r} )
Dialogue: 0.0:13:14.51.0:13:16.84.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}Much better.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:16.84.0:13:19.31.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:19.31.0:13:21.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Come in for a drink?
Dialogue: 0.0:13:25.25.0:13:28.76.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}Ah. Federation decor.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:28.75.0:13:30.25.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}Not your style?
Dialogue: 0.0:13:30.26.0:13:34.76.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Well. conformity\Nis not my style.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:34.76.0:13:37.26.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}What would you like?
Dialogue: 0.0:13:44.50.0:13:47.00.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I'd even like another.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:50.94.0:13:52.94.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Well. there she is again.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:52.94.0:13:54.44.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Counselor Troi.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:54.45.0:13:55.95.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}I'm not.
Dialogue: 0.0:13:57.45.0:14:00.45.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Computer. champagne.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:00.45.0:14:01.74.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}For two.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:11.93.0:14:16.44.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Am I moving too fast for you?
Dialogue: 0.0:14:16.43.0:14:20.93.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}No. I'm moving\Ntoo fast for me.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:20.94.0:14:23.44.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I like that better.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:28.28.0:14:33.12.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}I haven't been able to stop\Nthinking about you all day.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:50.45.0:14:53.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}You must have had\Na nice day.
Dialogue: 0.0:14:53.46.0:14:56.96.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Anticipation is fun.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:03.47.0:15:06.30.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}We'll be late for dinner.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:11.72.0:15:13.22.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Very late.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:27.77.0:15:29.27.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}Mr. Mendoza?
Dialogue: 0.0:15:29.27.0:15:31.77.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I seem to be a bit warm...
Dialogue: 0.0:15:33.28.0:15:35.28.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}I need some help here.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:36.66.0:15:40.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\hYou attempt to gain\Nevery unfair advantage. Picard.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:40.47.0:15:42.14.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}\hPremier Bhavani\Nhas no objection.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:42.14.0:15:44.01.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Well. I most certainly do.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:44.01.0:15:46.84.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}First. you conveniently\Narrange to play host
Dialogue: 0.0:15:46.84.0:15:49.26.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}then you plan\Nto send a manned probe
Dialogue: 0.0:15:49.26.0:15:50.66.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}into the wormhole.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:50.66.0:15:52.00.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}The Federation
Dialogue: 0.0:15:52.00.0:15:53.85.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}thinks it can do anything\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\hit wants to.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:53.85.0:15:55.35.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}Well. I will not tolerate it.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:55.35.0:15:58.11.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\hI will gladly share\Nthe results of our explorations
Dialogue: 0.0:15:58.60.0:15:59.60.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}with all the delegates.
Dialogue: 0.0:15:59.60.0:16:04.85.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}And you expect us to believe\N\h\h\h\h\h\hwhat you report?
Dialogue: 0.0:16:04.86.0:16:07.05.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Then send in your own probe.\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hGoss.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:07.05.0:16:09.05.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}\h\h\hThat's exactly\Nwhat I intend to do
Dialogue: 0.0:16:09.05.0:16:12.17.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}and I should strongly\Nsuggest that {\i1}you\N{\r}stay out of our way.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:18.76.0:16:22.05.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}\hTell Data and La Forge\Nto do themselves a favor
Dialogue: 0.0:16:22.04.0:16:23.79.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}and stay out of their way.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:26.90.0:16:30.80.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.408)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hCRUSHER:\N\h\h\h\hCaptain Picard.\Nplease come to Sick Bay.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:30.80.0:16:32.14.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}Acknowledged. Doctor.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:34.99.0:16:36.99.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}CRUSHER:\NWhatever he's got
Dialogue: 0.0:16:36.99.0:16:39.00.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}is obviously not\Nlife-threatening.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:38.99.0:16:42.49.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}It's some kind of system-wide\N\h\h\h\h\hhistaminic reaction.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:42.50.0:16:44.50.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}He certainly can't go back
Dialogue: 0.0:16:44.50.0:16:46.50.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}to negotiations\Nfor several days.
Dialogue: 0.0:16:46.50.0:16:49.51.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}Will you keep me informed?
Dialogue: 0.0:16:56.16.0:16:58.67.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}The Federation's\Ntop negotiator
Dialogue: 0.0:16:58.66.0:17:01.66.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}taken out\Nby a mysterious ailment.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:01.67.0:17:03.17.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Suspicions?
Dialogue: 0.0:17:03.17.0:17:05.17.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}With the Ferengi around?
Dialogue: 0.0:17:05.17.0:17:06.17.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}Always.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:06.17.0:17:07.67.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}You'll have to fill in.\NNumber One.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:07.67.0:17:08.68.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}Me?
Dialogue: 0.0:17:08.67.0:17:10.67.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Well. I'm\Nthe designated host.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:10.68.0:17:13.68.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}It would be\Na most awkward transition.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:13.68.0:17:15.68.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}You're the next likely choice.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:15.68.0:17:17.68.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}And Mr. Mendoza will\Ncertainly agree.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:17.68.0:17:21.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}He's quite impressed\Nby your natural instincts.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:21.19.0:17:23.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Excuse me. sir. but those\Nweren't natural instincts.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:23.69.0:17:25.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Those were poker instincts.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:25.19.0:17:27.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}A card game doesn't exactly\Nprepare me for this.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:27.19.0:17:30.20.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Yes. the stakes are higher.\Nbut then. isn't that
Dialogue: 0.0:17:30.19.0:17:32.52.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}when the game gets\Ninteresting. Commander?
Dialogue: 0.0:17:39.44.0:17:42.01.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}The wormhole will reappear\Nin 30 seconds. sir.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:42.01.0:17:44.51.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWORF:\NThe Ferengi pod is moving\N\h\h\h\h\h\hinto position.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:44.51.0:17:45.90.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}Shuttle 9. stand by.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:50.15.0:17:53.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}\h\h\h\h\hFerengi Pod. this is\NLieutenant Commander La Forge
Dialogue: 0.0:17:53.84.0:17:55.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}in the {\i1}Enterprise{\r} shuttle.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:55.84.0:17:58.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.408)}This is Dr. Arridor.\N\h\h\h\h\hGo ahead.
Dialogue: 0.0:17:58.34.0:18:00.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}Would you care to take\Nthe point. Doctor?
Dialogue: 0.0:18:00.34.0:18:05.57.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}We will gladly yield that honor\Nto you. Lieutenant Commander.
Dialogue: 0.0:18:07.38.0:18:09.39.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(334.432)}You know. if\Nthis doesn't work
Dialogue: 0.0:18:09.38.0:18:12.88.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}the thought of spending\Nthe rest of my life in here
Dialogue: 0.0:18:12.89.0:18:14.39.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}is none too appealing.
Dialogue: 0.0:18:14.39.0:18:16.39.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}There is a bright\Nside. Geordi.
Dialogue: 0.0:18:16.39.0:18:18.90.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}You will have me\Nto talk to.
Dialogue: 0.0:18:24.08.0:18:26.49.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.408)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hDATA:\NIt is visible. Captain.
Dialogue: 0.0:18:26.99.0:18:28.36.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}Proceed when ready.
Dialogue: 0.0:18:36.33.0:18:40.17.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.408)}\h\h\h\hDATA ( {\i1}distorted{\r} ):\N...and intense energy fields
Dialogue: 0.0:18:40.16.0:18:42.66.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.408)}which appear to be stabil...
Dialogue: 0.0:18:42.67.0:18:46.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}\h\hThey've traveled beyond our\Ncommunication capabilities. sir.
Dialogue: 0.0:18:46.45.0:18:47.76.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}A complete analysis of our bid
Dialogue: 0.0:18:47.77.0:18:50.53.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}is available on the ship's\Ncomputer for your consideration.
Dialogue: 0.0:18:52.04.0:18:54.35.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}\h\h\hCommander. I realize\Nwhat a difficult position
Dialogue: 0.0:18:54.36.0:18:55.20.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}this must be for you.
Dialogue: 0.0:18:55.20.0:18:57.52.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}If you don't\Nunderstand something
Dialogue: 0.0:18:57.52.0:19:00.22.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}\h\h\hI hope you won't be\Ntoo embarrassed to ask me.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:00.22.0:19:02.86.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}I think I have an idea\N\hwhat the rules are.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:02.85.0:19:05.73.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}Well. that's what makes it\N\h\h\h\h\hso interesting.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:05.74.0:19:08.55.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}\h\hThe rules of the game\Nchange to fit the moment.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:08.54.0:19:11.39.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}Not unlike commanding\Na starship. Mr. Ral.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:11.40.0:19:13.30.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}Well. Mr. Riker's placed a...
Dialogue: 0.0:19:13.30.0:19:15.80.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}a great deal of emphasis\N\h\h\h\h\h\hon defense--
Dialogue: 0.0:19:15.80.0:19:18.09.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}a subject he obviously\N\h\h\h\h\h\hknows well
Dialogue: 0.0:19:18.09.0:19:20.66.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}having served Starfleet
Dialogue: 0.0:19:20.66.0:19:23.23.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}in a number of conflicts.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:23.22.0:19:27.97.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Now. the Chrysalians--\Nwe're enemies to no one
Dialogue: 0.0:19:27.98.0:19:30.48.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}\h\h\hand we choose\Nto remain that way.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:30.48.0:19:32.49.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Neutral.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:32.48.0:19:34.98.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Neutral and uninvolved. sir
Dialogue: 0.0:19:35.49.0:19:40.38.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}in virtually all interstellar\N\h\h\hmatters of consequence.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:40.38.0:19:44.87.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}\h\h\h\hNo one would claim that\Nthe Chrysalians are as powerful
Dialogue: 0.0:19:44.86.0:19:48.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}as the mighty Federation.\N\h\hbut we have resources
Dialogue: 0.0:19:48.70.0:19:51.87.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}and technology\Nand scientists. too.
Dialogue: 0.0:19:51.87.0:19:54.86.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}But we also\Nhave had peace
Dialogue: 0.0:19:54.86.0:19:57.33.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}for ten generations.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:02.50.0:20:05.00.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(370.432)}RAL:\NYou know. I\Nwas thinking...
Dialogue: 0.0:20:05.00.0:20:06.50.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}TROI:\NMmm?
Dialogue: 0.0:20:06.50.0:20:10.01.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}RAL:\NMaybe I could stretch\Nout these negotiations
Dialogue: 0.0:20:10.00.0:20:11.00.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(370.432)}for a few days.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:11.01.0:20:12.51.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Would you like that?
Dialogue: 0.0:20:12.51.0:20:14.51.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}TROI:\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:19.10.0:20:22.60.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(370.432)}Devinoni Ral...
Dialogue: 0.0:20:22.60.0:20:25.11.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}who are you?
Dialogue: 0.0:20:25.10.0:20:29.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Well. what do your Betazoid\N\hsenses tell you about me?
Dialogue: 0.0:20:29.11.0:20:30.91.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}Not much.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:30.91.0:20:37.13.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}My human physical response\Nmust be blocking them out.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:37.13.0:20:39.59.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}Good.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:39.58.0:20:43.26.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}It never happened to me before.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:46.06.0:20:48.56.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}I rather like that I'm\Nmore difficult to read
Dialogue: 0.0:20:49.06.0:20:50.06.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}than your other men.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:50.06.0:20:55.97.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}There aren't any others...\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hcurrently.
Dialogue: 0.0:20:55.97.0:20:58.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}What about Commander Riker?
Dialogue: 0.0:21:04.71.0:21:07.21.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Who have you been\Ntalking to?
Dialogue: 0.0:21:07.21.0:21:08.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(370.432)}No one. No one.
Dialogue: 0.0:21:08.71.0:21:10.71.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}I just. uh...\Nsensed something
Dialogue: 0.0:21:10.72.0:21:13.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}when I saw the two\Nof you together.
Dialogue: 0.0:21:13.72.0:21:16.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Will Riker and I\Nare good friends.
Dialogue: 0.0:21:16.72.0:21:18.23.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(496.432)}Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0.0:21:26.90.0:21:30.04.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}It was once a little more\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hthan that.
Dialogue: 0.0:21:30.03.0:21:31.53.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}Ah...
Dialogue: 0.0:21:35.04.0:21:39.05.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}How come we're talking\Nabout me instead of you?
Dialogue: 0.0:21:39.04.0:21:43.54.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}Haven't you had enough people\Ntalk about their lives to you?
Dialogue: 0.0:21:43.55.0:21:45.55.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Who counsels the Counselor?
Dialogue: 0.0:21:45.55.0:21:46.55.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Oh. no.
Dialogue: 0.0:21:46.55.0:21:49.42.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}I want to know about you.
Dialogue: 0.0:21:49.42.0:21:52.86.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}I'm what you see right now.
Dialogue: 0.0:21:52.86.0:21:57.36.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}\hJust me... wanting\Nto run away with you
Dialogue: 0.0:21:57.36.0:22:01.77.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}but knowing you'd never\Nleave this damned ship.
Dialogue: 0.0:22:01.77.0:22:05.76.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}When I first saw you
Dialogue: 0.0:22:05.75.0:22:09.13.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}I felt as if I'd been waiting\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hfor you.
Dialogue: 0.0:22:09.14.0:22:11.85.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I'm trying to understand
Dialogue: 0.0:22:11.84.0:22:16.91.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}why or how that's possible.
Dialogue: 0.0:22:16.91.0:22:18.98.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Does it matter?
Dialogue: 0.0:22:23.89.0:22:27.39.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Well. it will. when I tell you.
Dialogue: 0.0:22:27.39.0:22:29.70.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}\h\h\hBut you must promise\Nnever to tell anyone else.
Dialogue: 0.0:22:29.69.0:22:32.47.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}What?
Dialogue: 0.0:22:35.45.0:22:37.67.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}I am part Betazoid. too.
Dialogue: 0.0:22:37.67.0:22:39.92.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}My mother was one-half.
Dialogue: 0.0:22:40.42.0:22:41.93.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}I am one-quarter.
Dialogue: 0.0:22:41.92.0:22:44.25.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}You're empathic?
Dialogue: 0.0:22:44.26.0:22:47.20.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}The only one of five children.
Dialogue: 0.0:22:47.19.0:22:51.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}And I must admit. I was...\NI was never as comfortable
Dialogue: 0.0:22:51.70.0:22:54.54.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}\hsensing emotions\Nas you seem to be.
Dialogue: 0.0:22:54.54.0:22:57.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}So that's why you left Earth.
Dialogue: 0.0:22:57.72.0:23:00.51.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(316.432)}Yes.
Dialogue: 0.0:23:00.51.0:23:05.52.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}I learned to live with it.\N\h\h\huse it. as you have.
Dialogue: 0.0:23:05.51.0:23:08.51.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}But still...
Dialogue: 0.0:23:08.52.0:23:11.24.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}it isolates us. doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0.0:23:11.24.0:23:13.54.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}And I thought\Nit always would
Dialogue: 0.0:23:14.04.0:23:16.38.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}so I tucked\Nmy heart away.
Dialogue: 0.0:23:16.37.0:23:18.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}I didn't need it.
Dialogue: 0.0:23:18.19.0:23:21.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}I didn't want it.
Dialogue: 0.0:23:21.20.0:23:30.21.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}\h\h\hAt the negotiating table.\Nit can be fatal to have a heart.
Dialogue: 0.0:23:30.20.0:23:34.70.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}\hBut I never realized\Nhow much I needed mine
Dialogue: 0.0:23:34.71.0:23:37.21.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}until I looked at you.
Dialogue: 0.0:23:52.44.0:23:54.67.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}I'm picking up an increase\Nin accretion matter
Dialogue: 0.0:23:54.68.0:23:56.25.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}filtering in\Nfrom the terminus.
Dialogue: 0.0:24:04.12.0:24:05.56.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Monitors are functioning\Nnormally again.
Dialogue: 0.0:24:05.56.0:24:07.36.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}Ferengi Pod...
Dialogue: 0.0:24:07.36.0:24:09.66.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}everybody in one piece\N\h\h\h\h\hover there?
Dialogue: 0.0:24:09.66.0:24:11.50.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.408)}\h\h\hARRIDOR:\NOur condition
Dialogue: 0.0:24:11.50.0:24:14.30.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.432)}is no concern of yours.\N{\i1}Enterprise{\r} Shuttle.
Dialogue: 0.0:24:14.30.0:24:17.55.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}We are competitors in this\Nventure. not partners.
Dialogue: 0.0:24:17.55.0:24:20.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.408)}Ferengi Pod out.
Dialogue: 0.0:24:20.32.0:24:22.83.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(388.432)}Happy landings\Nto you. too.
Dialogue: 0.0:24:22.82.0:24:24.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Curious.
Dialogue: 0.0:24:24.33.0:24:25.83.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(496.432)}Hmm?
Dialogue: 0.0:24:25.83.0:24:27.83.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}We are not where we\Nare supposed to be.
Dialogue: 0.0:24:27.83.0:24:29.33.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(334.432)}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0.0:24:29.33.0:24:31.33.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}We're on the other side\Nof the wormhole. aren't we?
Dialogue: 0.0:24:31.33.0:24:32.75.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}According to the Barzan probe
Dialogue: 0.0:24:33.25.0:24:34.75.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}\h\h\h\h\hwe should be\Nin the Gamma Quadrant
Dialogue: 0.0:24:34.75.0:24:36.76.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}but these readings\N\hclearly indicate
Dialogue: 0.0:24:36.75.0:24:38.25.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}\h\h\hwe are nearly\N200 light-years away
Dialogue: 0.0:24:38.26.0:24:41.04.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}in sector 3556
Dialogue: 0.0:24:41.04.0:24:42.73.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}of the Delta Quadrant.
Dialogue: 0.0:24:42.73.0:24:45.33.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}Maybe the Barzan readings\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\hwere wrong.
Dialogue: 0.0:24:45.33.0:24:49.22.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}Perhaps their readings\N\h\h\h\hwere correct.
Dialogue: 0.0:24:49.22.0:24:52.22.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}Their probe could have exited\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hthe wormhole
Dialogue: 0.0:24:52.22.0:24:54.22.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}at a completely different\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hlocation.
Dialogue: 0.0:24:54.22.0:24:56.48.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(316.432)}Hmm. Data. my\Nvisor's picking up
Dialogue: 0.0:24:56.47.0:24:58.25.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}subatomic fluctuations.
Dialogue: 0.0:24:58.26.0:25:01.77.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}Meson and lepton activity\Nis definitely increasing.
Dialogue: 0.0:25:01.76.0:25:04.56.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}Gravitational acceleration\N\h\h\his also increasing.
Dialogue: 0.0:25:06.48.0:25:10.36.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}\h\h\h\hSomething very strange\Nis happening to this wormhole.
Dialogue: 0.0:25:22.58.0:25:24.08.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0.0:25:29.59.0:25:32.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}You're unusually limber\Nthis morning.
Dialogue: 0.0:25:32.09.0:25:35.09.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}I'll say.
Dialogue: 0.0:25:35.10.0:25:37.60.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}Devinoni Ral.
Dialogue: 0.0:25:39.60.0:25:42.61.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}It's ridiculous\Nand wonderful.
Dialogue: 0.0:25:42.60.0:25:46.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}I feel completely\Nout of control.
Dialogue: 0.0:25:46.11.0:25:49.11.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Happy. terrified...
Dialogue: 0.0:25:49.11.0:25:52.62.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}but there's nothing\Nrational about this.
Dialogue: 0.0:25:52.61.0:25:56.11.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Who needs rational\Nwhen your toes curl up?
Dialogue: 0.0:26:01.12.0:26:05.61.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hI'm afraid\NI'm going to lose myself.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:05.61.0:26:07.90.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}I can't get enough of him.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:07.90.0:26:08.65.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}Is it possible
Dialogue: 0.0:26:09.15.0:26:10.65.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}to fall in love\Nin one day?
Dialogue: 0.0:26:11.15.0:26:12.40.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}I did.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:12.40.0:26:15.07.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}It was like this\Nfor you and Jack?
Dialogue: 0.0:26:15.07.0:26:17.56.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}No. it was another fellow.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:17.56.0:26:19.56.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}I fell in love in a day.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:19.56.0:26:22.56.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}It lasted a week.\Nbut what a week.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:25.43.0:26:27.37.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Then I met Jack.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:27.36.0:26:30.36.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Took months to figure it out\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hwith him.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:30.37.0:26:33.84.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}Well. then maybe I\Nshould slow down.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:33.84.0:26:35.39.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Catch my breath.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:35.39.0:26:40.15.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}Not let this thing\Nget out of control.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:40.14.0:26:43.12.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}BOTH:\NNah.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:43.13.0:26:45.40.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}I get no complaints.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:45.90.0:26:47.40.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}( {\i1}chuckles{\r} )
Dialogue: 0.0:26:47.40.0:26:48.41.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Uh. no.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:53.41.0:26:54.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Hi.
Dialogue: 0.0:26:57.46.0:26:59.47.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}To be honest.\NI was surprised
Dialogue: 0.0:26:59.46.0:27:02.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}to see the Caldonians\Nhere at all. Leyor.
Dialogue: 0.0:27:02.47.0:27:05.97.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}You must think Caldonia\Nvery insular. Mr. Ral.
Dialogue: 0.0:27:05.97.0:27:07.47.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}Oh. no. no. not\Nat all. not at all.
Dialogue: 0.0:27:07.47.0:27:10.48.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}On the contrary.\NI've always respected
Dialogue: 0.0:27:10.47.0:27:13.97.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.432)}your world's commitment\Nto pure research.
Dialogue: 0.0:27:13.98.0:27:15.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}It's just that...
Dialogue: 0.0:27:15.31.0:27:17.16.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(496.432)}well...
Dialogue: 0.0:27:17.16.0:27:19.16.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Go on. please.
Dialogue: 0.0:27:19.17.0:27:23.57.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Well. scholars don't always\Nenjoy administrative demands
Dialogue: 0.0:27:23.57.0:27:25.58.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(370.432)}and certainly\Nwe've seen here
Dialogue: 0.0:27:25.57.0:27:27.43.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}that the administration
Dialogue: 0.0:27:27.44.0:27:28.90.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}of the wormhole is...
Dialogue: 0.0:27:28.89.0:27:30.39.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Yes. I must admit
Dialogue: 0.0:27:30.39.0:27:34.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I have begun to feel\Nsome trepidation about that.
Dialogue: 0.0:27:36.62.0:27:37.62.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}Yes.
Dialogue: 0.0:27:37.62.0:27:40.54.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Yes. I'm sure you have. Leyor.
Dialogue: 0.0:27:40.54.0:27:42.96.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}I'm sure we all have.
Dialogue: 0.0:27:42.96.0:27:45.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Do you realize that\Nin the next century
Dialogue: 0.0:27:45.46.0:27:48.30.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}the number of ships\Nthat will pass...
Dialogue: 0.0:27:48.30.0:27:50.15.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Gentlemen. this open session
Dialogue: 0.0:27:50.15.0:27:53.15.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}\h\h\h\his called by request\Nof the Caldonian delegation.
Dialogue: 0.0:27:55.15.0:27:56.15.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Madame Bhavani
Dialogue: 0.0:27:56.15.0:27:59.65.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}\h\h\hCaldonia withdraws\Nfrom these proceedings.
Dialogue: 0.0:27:59.66.0:28:02.00.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(370.432)}For what\Nreasons. Leyor?
Dialogue: 0.0:28:01.99.0:28:03.44.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}It has been made very clear
Dialogue: 0.0:28:03.44.0:28:05.94.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\hthat the maintenance\Nand administrative requirements
Dialogue: 0.0:28:05.95.0:28:07.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}are beyond our abilities.
Dialogue: 0.0:28:07.31.0:28:10.44.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}\hLeyor. the Federation\Nwould like to negotiate
Dialogue: 0.0:28:10.45.0:28:11.71.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}a trade agreement
Dialogue: 0.0:28:11.70.0:28:14.23.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}in which we could acquire\Nyour planet's rich deposits
Dialogue: 0.0:28:14.24.0:28:17.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hof trillium 323.\Nwhich we would add to our bid
Dialogue: 0.0:28:17.46.0:28:19.18.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Premier Bhavani.
Dialogue: 0.0:28:19.18.0:28:20.48.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.432)}My apologies.
Dialogue: 0.0:28:20.48.0:28:21.98.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}We have already reached\N\h\h\h\h\h\han agreement
Dialogue: 0.0:28:22.48.0:28:23.35.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}with the Chrysalians.
Dialogue: 0.0:28:30.32.0:28:31.16.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Mr. Ral
Dialogue: 0.0:28:31.16.0:28:33.01.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}\h\h\hyou either had\Nvery good instincts
Dialogue: 0.0:28:33.01.0:28:36.23.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}\h\h\h\h\hor a foreknowledge\Nof the Caldonian withdrawal.
Dialogue: 0.0:28:36.23.0:28:38.05.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}Well. some people\N\hjust don't like
Dialogue: 0.0:28:38.05.0:28:40.55.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}to transact business\Nwith the Federation
Dialogue: 0.0:28:40.55.0:28:42.77.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}Commander.
Dialogue: 0.0:28:42.77.0:28:46.52.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}The Chrysalians hereby add\Nthe Caldonian trillium 323
Dialogue: 0.0:28:46.52.0:28:48.98.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}to its bid. Premier.
Dialogue: 0.0:28:58.25.0:29:00.25.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I'm telling you. it's changing.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:00.25.0:29:02.04.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.408)}I can see it with my VISOR.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:02.04.0:29:04.04.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}I have no intention\N\h\hof leaving yet.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:04.04.0:29:06.54.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}We have not finished\Ntaking our readings.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:06.54.0:29:07.38.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.408)}Listen. Doctor.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:07.37.0:29:09.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(316.432)}Your readings must\Nbe telling you
Dialogue: 0.0:29:09.33.0:29:10.83.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(370.432)}the same things\Nwe're getting.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:10.83.0:29:12.13.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(370.432)}This is not the\NGamma Quadrant.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:12.13.0:29:14.90.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}I will not confirm\Nyour speculations.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:14.90.0:29:16.87.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}This is not a speculation.\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hDoctor.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:16.87.0:29:18.87.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}We are not where the Barzans\N\h\h\h\h\hsaid we should be
Dialogue: 0.0:29:18.87.0:29:20.16.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}which would indicate
Dialogue: 0.0:29:20.44.0:29:22.93.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.408)}this side of the wormhole\N\h\h\h\h\h\his not stable.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:22.92.0:29:24.83.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}There are meson and lepton\N\h\h\h\h\h\hfluctuations.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:24.84.0:29:27.85.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}\h\hLocal gravitational fields\Nare increasing exponentially.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:27.85.0:29:30.15.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}Everything says we better\Nget the hell out of here.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:30.15.0:29:32.49.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}It will be visible again\N\h\h\hin... 40 seconds.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:32.98.0:29:34.81.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\hWe will make\Nour own judgments then.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:34.82.0:29:36.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}\hI can see it now.\Nand I'm telling you
Dialogue: 0.0:29:36.72.0:29:39.23.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}you don't have time to wait.\N\h\h\h\hnot even 40 seconds.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:39.22.0:29:40.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.408)}Ferengi Pod out.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:40.72.0:29:41.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}Damn it. Arridor!
Dialogue: 0.0:29:41.73.0:29:44.50.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}We're 70.000\Nlight-years
Dialogue: 0.0:29:44.50.0:29:46.37.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}away from our ships.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:46.36.0:29:47.86.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Come on now-- follow us in.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:47.87.0:29:49.15.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}We'll lead you.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:52.49.0:29:53.99.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Idiots.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:56.49.0:29:57.99.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}It's getting worse.
Dialogue: 0.0:29:57.99.0:30:00.25.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}I'm taking us in. Data
Dialogue: 0.0:30:00.24.0:30:01.86.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}with or without them.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:01.86.0:30:03.64.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Thrusters at half power.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:03.65.0:30:05.02.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}Three-quarters.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:05.02.0:30:07.02.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Entering outer\Nevent horizon.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:13.56.0:30:16.86.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(316.432)}They panic quickly\Nunder pressure.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:18.93.0:30:20.27.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}There.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:20.26.0:30:21.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.432)}Precisely as scheduled.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:21.70.0:30:24.09.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(316.432)}Right where I\Nexpected it to be.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:27.34.0:30:28.74.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(442.432)}( {\i1}gasping{\r} )
Dialogue: 0.0:30:35.13.0:30:36.63.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}Everyone was talking today
Dialogue: 0.0:30:37.13.0:30:40.14.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}about the way you absorbed\Nthe Caldonian bid.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:40.13.0:30:42.13.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Well. the opening\Nwas there.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:42.14.0:30:43.64.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}I took it.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:43.64.0:30:46.64.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Commander Riker didn't know\Nhow you managed it.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:46.64.0:30:50.03.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}Let me tell you something\N\h\habout Commander Riker.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:50.03.0:30:51.53.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}He's good.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:51.53.0:30:54.87.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}He's the most dangerous man\N\h\h\h\hin that room to me.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:54.87.0:30:58.64.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}But he doesn't have an edge...
Dialogue: 0.0:30:58.64.0:30:59.97.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}your edge.
Dialogue: 0.0:30:59.97.0:31:01.81.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}{\i1}Our{\r} edge.
Dialogue: 0.0:31:01.81.0:31:04.81.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}You make it sound unethical.
Dialogue: 0.0:31:04.81.0:31:07.30.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0.0:31:07.29.0:31:11.74.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Deanna. it's just business.
Dialogue: 0.0:31:17.10.0:31:20.47.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Why haven't you told anyone\N\h\h\h\h\hyou're an empath?
Dialogue: 0.0:31:20.47.0:31:23.95.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}Because I find it makes people\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\huncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0.0:31:23.96.0:31:30.80.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}\hI think you don't tell them\Nso you can gain an advantage.
Dialogue: 0.0:31:30.80.0:31:34.04.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Well. I gained an advantage\N\h\h\hby using it with you.
Dialogue: 0.0:31:34.04.0:31:36.44.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}You didn't seem\Nto mind that.
Dialogue: 0.0:31:42.60.0:31:44.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.432)}Look. Deanna.
Dialogue: 0.0:31:44.10.0:31:49.11.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}The point of negotiating\N\his to take advantage.
Dialogue: 0.0:31:49.10.0:31:51.60.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I don't know what the other side\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\his offering
Dialogue: 0.0:31:51.61.0:31:54.11.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}and they don't know\N\hwhat I'm offering
Dialogue: 0.0:31:54.11.0:31:57.03.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}so we dance around each other\N\h\h\h\h\huntil somebody wins.
Dialogue: 0.0:31:57.03.0:31:59.92.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}I never cry foul\Nwhen I lose.
Dialogue: 0.0:31:59.91.0:32:02.91.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}\h\hBut you're reading\Ntheir emotional states
Dialogue: 0.0:32:02.92.0:32:04.42.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}their inner selves
Dialogue: 0.0:32:04.42.0:32:06.92.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}and then using that\Nto manipulate them.
Dialogue: 0.0:32:06.92.0:32:10.14.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Well. people have been doing\Nthat for thousands of years
Dialogue: 0.0:32:10.14.0:32:12.01.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}just by listening\Ncarefully
Dialogue: 0.0:32:12.01.0:32:14.35.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}by-by watching\Nbody language.
Dialogue: 0.0:32:14.34.0:32:16.22.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}\h\h\hI just happen\Nto be better at it.
Dialogue: 0.0:32:16.23.0:32:17.57.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}You do it.
Dialogue: 0.0:32:17.56.0:32:23.01.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}I do it to help my crew.\N\h\hnot outmaneuver them
Dialogue: 0.0:32:23.52.0:32:25.53.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}\h\hand I don't hide\Nthat I'm an empath.
Dialogue: 0.0:32:25.52.0:32:26.82.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}Oh. so you\Nannounce it
Dialogue: 0.0:32:26.82.0:32:30.14.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}to every alien culture\N\h\h\h\hyou encounter?
Dialogue: 0.0:32:30.14.0:32:33.64.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hOr do you use it\Nto give your side an advantage?
Dialogue: 0.0:32:33.65.0:32:36.90.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Do you tell the Romulan\Nthat's about to attack
Dialogue: 0.0:32:36.90.0:32:39.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}\h\h\h\h\hthat you sense\Nthat he may be bluffing
Dialogue: 0.0:32:39.32.0:32:41.61.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}or do you just tell it\N\h\h\hto your Captain?
Dialogue: 0.0:32:47.46.0:32:48.97.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}That's different.
Dialogue: 0.0:32:49.46.0:32:51.76.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}That's a matter of protection.
Dialogue: 0.0:32:51.77.0:32:53.15.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}Yes. protection--
Dialogue: 0.0:32:53.15.0:32:57.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}\h\h\h\h{\i1}your{\r} protection.\Nyour Captain. your crew
Dialogue: 0.0:32:57.45.0:33:00.62.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}your edge.
Dialogue: 0.0:33:00.62.0:33:02.02.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(316.432)}Yes.
Dialogue: 0.0:33:02.03.0:33:05.03.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}Now. it's a matter\Nof life and death
Dialogue: 0.0:33:05.53.0:33:08.03.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}when you take the advantage.
Dialogue: 0.0:33:08.03.0:33:11.54.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Me. I deal in property.\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\hexchanges.
Dialogue: 0.0:33:11.54.0:33:13.37.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}Nobody gets hurt.
Dialogue: 0.0:33:13.37.0:33:16.63.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}So you tell me--
Dialogue: 0.0:33:16.62.0:33:19.45.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}which one of us would you say
Dialogue: 0.0:33:19.46.0:33:21.96.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}has more of a problem\N\h\h\h\h\hwith ethics?
Dialogue: 0.0:33:21.96.0:33:23.77.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0.0:33:52.71.0:33:56.22.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}May I join you.\NCommander?
Dialogue: 0.0:33:56.21.0:33:58.71.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Bought out\Nthe Ferengi yet. Ral?
Dialogue: 0.0:33:58.72.0:34:00.22.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}Think I should\Ngive it a try?
Dialogue: 0.0:34:00.22.0:34:01.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}No. but I think\Nthat you will.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:01.72.0:34:02.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}One way or another
Dialogue: 0.0:34:03.22.0:34:04.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}it's going to come down\Nto you and me.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:04.72.0:34:06.23.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}You know. you're\Nvery good at this.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:06.22.0:34:07.57.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(460.432)}Very good.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:07.57.0:34:09.07.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(334.432)}Much better\Nthan you realize.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:09.08.0:34:11.08.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Well. I hope I'm better\Nthan you realize.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:11.08.0:34:13.33.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}The last mile\Nof the marathon
Dialogue: 0.0:34:13.33.0:34:15.15.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}is always the toughest.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:15.15.0:34:17.87.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}That's when the\Nwinners are willing\Nto take the big risks.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:17.87.0:34:19.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}You willing to do that?
Dialogue: 0.0:34:19.69.0:34:20.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}We'll see. won't we?
Dialogue: 0.0:34:20.69.0:34:22.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Well. let's see now.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:22.19.0:34:25.16.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}I'm prepared to reach a firm\Nagreement with Bhavani
Dialogue: 0.0:34:25.16.0:34:28.16.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}before we learn the outcome\Nof your probe's expedition.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:28.16.0:34:31.08.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(496.432)}Are you?
Dialogue: 0.0:34:31.08.0:34:32.59.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Well. well. well.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:32.58.0:34:35.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}That would not be\Nlooked upon favorably
Dialogue: 0.0:34:35.47.0:34:37.47.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(316.432)}by the Federation.\NI'd imagine.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:37.47.0:34:41.81.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}You see. you have\Nto be willing to take\Nthat last step alone
Dialogue: 0.0:34:41.81.0:34:43.26.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}or it just isn't\Nworth playing.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:43.26.0:34:45.26.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Your point of\Nview. not mine.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:45.26.0:34:47.27.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}Oh. I see that.\NCommander. I see that.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:47.26.0:34:50.71.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}Otherwise. you wouldn't be\N\h\h\h\h\h{\i1}second{\r} in command
Dialogue: 0.0:34:50.72.0:34:52.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(334.432)}of this starship.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:52.19.0:34:54.47.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(496.432)}You know
Dialogue: 0.0:34:54.47.0:34:59.36.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}I feel responsible for you\N\h\h\hin a way... related.
Dialogue: 0.0:34:59.36.0:35:00.70.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Deanna.
Dialogue: 0.0:35:02.51.0:35:04.47.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}We both love Deanna.
Dialogue: 0.0:35:04.48.0:35:07.49.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}Oh. in different ways.\N\h\h\h\h\h\hof course.
Dialogue: 0.0:35:07.48.0:35:10.90.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}\hI will remove that burden\Nof responsibility right now.
Dialogue: 0.0:35:10.90.0:35:14.18.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}My relationship with Deanna\Nstands very well on its own
Dialogue: 0.0:35:14.19.0:35:15.58.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}without any\Nhelp from you.
Dialogue: 0.0:35:15.58.0:35:17.08.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}Of course it does.\Nof course it does.
Dialogue: 0.0:35:17.08.0:35:20.58.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}It's just that. well...
Dialogue: 0.0:35:20.58.0:35:23.09.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}She's a remarkable woman.
Dialogue: 0.0:35:23.08.0:35:27.58.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}Brilliant. lovely...
Dialogue: 0.0:35:27.59.0:35:29.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}very passionate.
Dialogue: 0.0:35:29.34.0:35:31.99.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}And she could have\Nbeen yours. Will.
Dialogue: 0.0:35:31.99.0:35:35.95.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}But you just didn't do enough\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hto keep her.
Dialogue: 0.0:35:35.95.0:35:38.95.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}And now. well...
Dialogue: 0.0:35:38.95.0:35:40.95.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}I'm here
Dialogue: 0.0:35:41.45.0:35:43.76.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}and I'm going to take her. too.
Dialogue: 0.0:35:47.17.0:35:50.04.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}That's the first bad play\N\h\h\hI've seen you make.
Dialogue: 0.0:35:50.04.0:35:53.74.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}If you can bring happiness\Ninto Deanna's life
Dialogue: 0.0:35:53.75.0:35:55.38.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}nothing would\Nplease me more.
Dialogue: 0.0:35:55.88.0:35:58.88.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}You know. you're really\Nnot such a bad sort. Ral
Dialogue: 0.0:35:59.39.0:36:01.39.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}except you don't\Nhave any values--
Dialogue: 0.0:36:01.39.0:36:04.26.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}beyond the value\Nof today's bid. that is.
Dialogue: 0.0:36:04.26.0:36:09.70.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Deanna is just the woman\Nto bring some meaning
Dialogue: 0.0:36:09.70.0:36:11.65.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}to your sorry existence
Dialogue: 0.0:36:12.15.0:36:14.15.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}if you're smart enough\Nto take it.
Dialogue: 0.0:36:14.15.0:36:17.16.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I doubt that you are.
Dialogue: 0.0:36:17.15.0:36:19.65.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}To the last mile.
Dialogue: 0.0:36:32.54.0:36:36.93.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Sir. the Ferengi vessel\Nis moving out of orbit.
Dialogue: 0.0:36:36.92.0:36:38.92.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}Impulse power.
Dialogue: 0.0:36:38.93.0:36:42.93.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}They are approaching\Nthe entry to the\Nwormhole. sir.
Dialogue: 0.0:36:42.93.0:36:45.94.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}Computer. is the Ferengi Goss\Nstill on board the {\i1}Enterprise?
Dialogue: 0.0:36:46.43.0:36:48.93.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.408)}\h\h\h\h\hDaiMon Goss departed\Nthe {\i1}Enterprise{\r} at 1400 hours.
Dialogue: 0.0:36:48.94.0:36:50.94.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(334.432)}They are powering\Nforward missile\Nlaunchers. sir.
Dialogue: 0.0:36:50.94.0:36:52.44.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.432)}Yellow Alert.
Dialogue: 0.0:36:52.44.0:36:54.28.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}Hail the Ferengi.
Dialogue: 0.0:36:56.09.0:36:58.09.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}\h\h\h\hRequest an explanation\Nof your actions. DaiMon Goss.
Dialogue: 0.0:36:58.10.0:37:01.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.408)}I've learned from informed\Nsources that the Federation
Dialogue: 0.0:37:01.60.0:37:03.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.408)}\hhas manipulated\Nthese negotiations
Dialogue: 0.0:37:03.10.0:37:04.47.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.408)}from the very beginning
Dialogue: 0.0:37:04.97.0:37:07.92.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.408)}and has already signed a secret\N\h\hagreement with the Barzans.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:07.92.0:37:09.26.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}That is not true.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:09.26.0:37:12.08.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.408)}\h\h\hThe Ferengi offer was\Nnever seriously considered.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:12.08.0:37:16.05.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Premier Bhavani welcomed you\N\h\h\h\hto these proceedings
Dialogue: 0.0:37:16.05.0:37:17.80.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}despite my better judgment.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:17.80.0:37:21.32.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.408)}We will be ignored no longer.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:21.32.0:37:23.99.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}They fired a missile\Ndirectly at the\Nopening. sir.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:23.99.0:37:24.89.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}Destroy it.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:24.89.0:37:25.89.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(460.432)}On screen.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:25.89.0:37:28.16.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(370.432)}Firing phasers.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:31.96.0:37:36.42.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Your offers both\Nhave merit. gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:36.42.0:37:38.42.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}If I could find\Na deciding factor...
Dialogue: 0.0:37:38.42.0:37:39.42.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}( {\i1}alarm blaring{\r} )
Dialogue: 0.0:37:39.42.0:37:40.42.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Riker to Picard.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:40.42.0:37:42.29.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}What's happening.\NCaptain?
Dialogue: 0.0:37:42.29.0:37:44.71.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Goss has fired a missile\N\h\h\h\hat the wormhole.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:44.71.0:37:45.98.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.408)}I need you on the Bridge.\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\hNumber One.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:46.48.0:37:47.98.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0.0:37:50.35.0:37:54.24.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}\h\h\h\hExcuse me for saying so\Nunder the circumstances. Premier
Dialogue: 0.0:37:54.23.0:37:56.73.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}but... this fight\Nseems to really be
Dialogue: 0.0:37:56.74.0:37:59.74.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}between the Federation\N\h\h\hand the Ferengi.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:00.24.0:38:03.25.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}Now. it seems unconscionable\N\h\h\h\h\hthat your wormhole
Dialogue: 0.0:38:03.24.0:38:07.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}is being used as a pawn\Nin their power struggle.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:07.70.0:38:10.65.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}You must know we will not\N\h\hallow you to do this.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:10.65.0:38:13.66.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.408)}If the Ferengi cannot have\Nthe wormhole. no one will.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:13.65.0:38:16.48.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}\h\h\h\h\hA missile will have no\Ndestructive effect on a wormhole
Dialogue: 0.0:38:16.49.0:38:18.91.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}but. if it should explode\N\h\hnear the shuttlecraft
Dialogue: 0.0:38:18.91.0:38:20.41.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}they will be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:20.41.0:38:22.42.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.408)}Casualties of war. Captain.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:22.41.0:38:24.41.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.408)}My men are prepared to die.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:24.41.0:38:25.74.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.408)}Are yours?
Dialogue: 0.0:38:25.75.0:38:27.39.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Captain.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:27.38.0:38:29.11.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}He's lying.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:29.12.0:38:30.52.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}I'm almost sure if it.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:30.52.0:38:31.81.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}He doesn't mean what he says.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:31.81.0:38:34.61.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}Why? What is he\Ndoing it for. then?
Dialogue: 0.0:38:38.30.0:38:39.67.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Permission to enter\Nthe Bridge. Captain.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:39.66.0:38:41.57.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Premier. with all due respect...
Dialogue: 0.0:38:41.58.0:38:42.47.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}RAL:\NCaptain.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:42.47.0:38:44.42.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(334.432)}I believe I am in\Na better position
Dialogue: 0.0:38:44.42.0:38:45.67.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}to settle this\Nwith DaiMon Goss
Dialogue: 0.0:38:45.67.0:38:48.01.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}than you are.
Dialogue: 0.0:38:48.00.0:38:50.00.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}May I address him?
Dialogue: 0.0:38:50.01.0:38:51.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Premier?
Dialogue: 0.0:39:00.25.0:39:02.05.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(424.432)}DaiMon Goss?
Dialogue: 0.0:39:02.05.0:39:03.29.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}This is Devinoni Ral.
Dialogue: 0.0:39:03.79.0:39:05.69.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.408)}I have nothing to say\N\h\h\h\h\hto you. Ral.
Dialogue: 0.0:39:05.69.0:39:07.79.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.432)}Well. then just listen.
Dialogue: 0.0:39:07.79.0:39:13.30.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}The planet Barzan has\Nreached an agreement\Nwith the Chrysalians
Dialogue: 0.0:39:13.30.0:39:14.63.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}for long-term control\Nof the wormhole.
Dialogue: 0.0:39:14.63.0:39:16.55.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Now. on behalf\Nof the Chrysalians
Dialogue: 0.0:39:16.55.0:39:18.30.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I am prepared to offer\Nthe Ferengi
Dialogue: 0.0:39:18.30.0:39:22.17.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hfree access\Nto the wormhole in perpetuity.
Dialogue: 0.0:39:22.17.0:39:23.51.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.408)}I have your word on this?
Dialogue: 0.0:39:23.51.0:39:25.91.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(316.432)}Yes. my word. sir.
Dialogue: 0.0:39:25.91.0:39:29.28.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(226.432)}In exchange for Ferengi\Nconvoy privileges
Dialogue: 0.0:39:29.28.0:39:31.28.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}to be negotiated in good faith.
Dialogue: 0.0:39:31.72.0:39:33.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.408)}This is an acceptable offer.
Dialogue: 0.0:39:33.18.0:39:38.16.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}The Ferengi vessel has shut down\N\hits forward missile launcher.
Dialogue: 0.0:39:38.17.0:39:40.18.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Stand down Red Alert.
Dialogue: 0.0:39:40.17.0:39:42.77.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}Commander Riker
Dialogue: 0.0:39:42.78.0:39:44.83.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}I'm sorry you\Nhad to learn
Dialogue: 0.0:39:44.83.0:39:47.13.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}about my decision this way.
Dialogue: 0.0:39:47.13.0:39:49.42.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}\h\hYou represented\Nthe Federation well
Dialogue: 0.0:39:49.42.0:39:52.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}but I have come to believe\Nthat the Chrysalians'
Dialogue: 0.0:39:52.10.0:39:56.31.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\htradition of peace\Nis more desirable to my planet.
Dialogue: 0.0:39:56.31.0:39:57.99.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}Excuse me. Premier.
Dialogue: 0.0:39:57.99.0:39:59.48.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(334.432)}There's something\Nyou should know.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:01.14.0:40:02.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(460.432)}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:02.46.0:40:05.96.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}Was there something\Nyou wanted to say?
Dialogue: 0.0:40:05.97.0:40:07.97.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}No. not at all.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:07.97.0:40:10.62.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}I sensed you suddenly\N\hfelt uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:10.62.0:40:14.81.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWell. after all.\Nit was a very tense situation.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:14.81.0:40:16.70.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}But that's what's so odd.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:16.69.0:40:18.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}It wasn't tense at all.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:18.70.0:40:20.50.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}In fact. I sensed no tension
Dialogue: 0.0:40:20.50.0:40:23.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}from you or Goss.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:23.10.0:40:24.50.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.408)}I was tense!
Dialogue: 0.0:40:24.50.0:40:26.01.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.408)}I was ready to blow it up.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:26.00.0:40:27.30.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.408)}Wha... I strongly protest!
Dialogue: 0.0:40:27.30.0:40:29.01.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}Screen off.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:29.02.0:40:30.53.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(352.432)}It was as though
Dialogue: 0.0:40:30.52.0:40:32.92.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}you were performing a scene\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\hfor all of us.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:32.93.0:40:34.40.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}Pardon me. Captain.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:34.89.0:40:37.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I... I believe there's a slight\N\h\h\hconflict of interest here.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:37.73.0:40:40.37.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(334.432)}I agree entirely.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:40.37.0:40:43.12.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}\hMr. Ral asked me\Nnot to tell anyone
Dialogue: 0.0:40:43.12.0:40:44.96.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}he has empathic powers
Dialogue: 0.0:40:44.96.0:40:48.16.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(370.432)}which he uses\Nto manipulate\Nhis competitors
Dialogue: 0.0:40:48.16.0:40:51.03.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}in a negotiation.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:51.03.0:40:54.15.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}\hAnd. yes. it did put me\Nin a conflict of interest
Dialogue: 0.0:40:54.15.0:40:56.65.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(172.432)}\h\h\h\hwhich I hope\NI have now resolved.
Dialogue: 0.0:40:56.65.0:40:59.02.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}Premier. I believe Ral
Dialogue: 0.0:40:59.02.0:41:01.34.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(208.432)}has used your fear\Nof continuing aggression
Dialogue: 0.0:41:01.34.0:41:04.16.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}between the Federation\N\h\h\hand its enemies
Dialogue: 0.0:41:04.16.0:41:05.91.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}to undermine our position.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:05.91.0:41:08.20.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(388.432)}I also believe
Dialogue: 0.0:41:08.19.0:41:11.16.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}\h\h\h\hthat this incident\Nwas staged by Ral and Goss
Dialogue: 0.0:41:11.16.0:41:12.66.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}to provide you a reason
Dialogue: 0.0:41:12.67.0:41:15.55.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(298.432)}to choose in favor\Nof the Chrysalians.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:15.55.0:41:17.47.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Captain
Dialogue: 0.0:41:17.47.0:41:18.36.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}it's the shuttlecraft.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:18.36.0:41:19.66.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}They're coming\Nback through.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:22.33.0:41:24.95.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.408)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hLA FORGE:\NShuttle 9 to {\i1}Enterprise.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:24.94.0:41:26.56.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(460.432)}On screen.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:28.06.0:41:31.06.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.408)}This is Shuttle 9 reporting in.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:31.07.0:41:32.49.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(514.432)}Barely.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:32.94.0:41:34.94.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.408)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hPICARD:\NAnd the Ferengi pod. Commander?
Dialogue: 0.0:41:34.94.0:41:36.94.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}Trapped on\Nthe other side. sir.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:36.94.0:41:38.36.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.408)}In Delta Quadrant.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:38.36.0:41:39.36.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.408)}We tried to warn them.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:39.36.0:41:40.86.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.408)}They wouldn't follow us.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:41.36.0:41:42.36.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}Elaborate.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:42.36.0:41:45.82.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Captain. this end of the\Nwormhole is currently stable
Dialogue: 0.0:41:45.82.0:41:50.12.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}but the other end apparently\Nshifts positions periodically.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:50.12.0:41:53.96.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.408)}The Barzan probe had no way\N\h\h\h\h\hto recognize this.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:53.96.0:41:56.71.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.408)}Eventually. both sides\N\h\hwill be unstable.
Dialogue: 0.0:41:57.21.0:42:00.18.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.408)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hLA FORGE:\NIt's a dry well. Captain.\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hworthless.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:00.18.0:42:01.28.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}Acknowledged. Shuttle.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:01.28.0:42:04.29.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}\h\h\h\h\hMain Shuttle Bay.\Nprepare for final approach.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:04.28.0:42:05.64.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.384)}Aye. sir.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:05.65.0:42:08.07.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}WORF:\NCaptain. DaiMon Goss\Nis demanding
Dialogue: 0.0:42:08.07.0:42:10.63.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(406.432)}to know where\Nhis men are.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:10.62.0:42:13.40.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(190.432)}Advise him to set\N\hhis coordinates
Dialogue: 0.0:42:13.41.0:42:14.91.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}for the Delta Quadrant.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:14.91.0:42:18.92.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}He may run into them\Nin... 80 years or so.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:20.77.0:42:22.77.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}Mr. Ral...
Dialogue: 0.0:42:22.77.0:42:24.77.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}congratulations\Non winning the rights
Dialogue: 0.0:42:25.27.0:42:26.53.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}to the Barzan wormhole.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:26.52.0:42:30.39.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}I take the risks. Mr. Riker
Dialogue: 0.0:42:30.39.0:42:33.26.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}and I stand by my agreements.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:37.20.0:42:38.70.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(496.432)}Come in.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:46.21.0:42:48.21.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}When do you leave?
Dialogue: 0.0:42:48.21.0:42:49.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}Soon.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:49.71.0:42:52.09.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I've been recalled\Nby the Chrysalians.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:52.10.0:42:54.57.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Explanations demanded.\Nand so forth.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:54.57.0:42:56.46.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(262.432)}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:56.45.0:42:58.55.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}Well. I've done well for them\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\hover the years.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:58.56.0:42:59.89.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.432)}They understand the stakes.
Dialogue: 0.0:42:59.89.0:43:03.06.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}It'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:03.89.0:43:05.75.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}I had to do it. Troi.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:05.76.0:43:09.10.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}Bhavani was ready to go\Nwith the Federation.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:09.10.0:43:11.02.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(244.432)}I sensed it.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:11.52.0:43:14.02.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(154.432)}I'd used up every card\N\h\h\h\h\hin the deck.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:14.02.0:43:16.28.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(82.432)}I needed to change the rules.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:16.27.0:43:19.42.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}\h\h\h\h\h\hYou must have known\NI couldn't allow you to do that.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:19.43.0:43:22.38.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(118.432)}My human physical response
Dialogue: 0.0:43:22.38.0:43:26.75.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}must have been blocking\N\h\hmy Betazoid senses.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:30.75.0:43:34.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I'm very grateful\Nfor what you did. in a way.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:34.72.0:43:38.72.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}It's made me take a hard look\Nat who I am.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:39.23.0:43:41.23.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I don't like what I see.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:41.23.0:43:45.94.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}I once asked you\Nto run away with me.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:45.94.0:43:48.71.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}And now I'm asking again.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:48.71.0:43:50.21.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.432)}I need you.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:50.21.0:43:53.21.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}You could help me change.
Dialogue: 0.0:43:53.21.0:43:55.58.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(64.432)}You could...\Nyou could be my conscience.
Dialogue: 0.0:44:10.53.0:44:13.87.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(280.432)}I already have a job\Nas counselor.
Dialogue: 0.0:44:27.58.0:44:31.18.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(136.120)}[Captioning sponsored by\N\h\h\hPARAMOUNT PICTURES
Dialogue: 0.0:44:31.18.0:44:35.19.Default..0.0.0..{\an1\pos(100.144)}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hCaptioned by\N\h\h\h\h\hThe Caption Center\NWGBH Educational Foundation]
